f3TwampIpInterfaceTable.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceTable
f3TwampIpInterfaceTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to TWAMP IP Interfaces that are used for the TWAMP. These IP interfaces facilitate generation and reception of TWAMP Control and Test packets.

f3TwampIpInterfaceEntry.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceEntry
f3TwampIpInterfaceEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampIpInterfaceTable.

f3TwampIpInterfaceName.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceName
f3TwampIpInterfaceName.description: Name of the TWAMP IP interface.

f3TwampIpInterfacePort.name: f3TwampIpInterfacePort
f3TwampIpInterfacePort.description: This is the physical or logical port on which the TWAMP IP Interface is associated with.

f3TwampIpInterfaceIpMode.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceIpMode
f3TwampIpInterfaceIpMode.description: This object is the ipmode of TWAMP IP Interface and indicates if the interface is IPv4-only or IPv4-and-IPv6. Currently it is read-only and will be set to IPv4 Only.

f3TwampIpInterfaceIpv4Address.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceIpv4Address
f3TwampIpInterfaceIpv4Address.description: IPv4 Address of the TWAMP IP Interface.

f3TwampIpInterfaceIpv4Mask.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceIpv4Mask
f3TwampIpInterfaceIpv4Mask.description: IPv4 Mask of the TWAMP IP Interface.

f3TwampIpInterfaceStorageType.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceStorageType
f3TwampIpInterfaceStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

f3TwampIpInterfaceRowStatus.name: f3TwampIpInterfaceRowStatus
f3TwampIpInterfaceRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of f3TwampIpInterfaceRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with f3TwampIpInterfaceRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The f3TwampIpInterfaceRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

f3TwampServerTable.name: f3TwampServerTable
f3TwampServerTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to TWAMP Server entities. This entity performs the functions of TWAMP Server when TWAMP Control protocol is enabled as defined in RFC 5357. This entity is created even when TWAMP Control is disabled as a container for Session Reflectors.

f3TwampServerEntry.name: f3TwampServerEntry
f3TwampServerEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampServerTable.

f3TwampServerIndex.name: f3TwampServerIndex
f3TwampServerIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a TWAMP Server under the NE.

f3TwampServerAdminState.name: f3TwampServerAdminState
f3TwampServerAdminState.description: All the state related attributes are added to support this entity being in outage state. But AdminState is always InService and is not editable.

f3TwampServerOperationalState.name: f3TwampServerOperationalState
f3TwampServerOperationalState.description: Operational state can take Normal or Outage. When the TWAMP entity is operational then this is Normal. In some situations like a Card is unplugged and TWAMP entity is not operational this attribute goes to Outage state.

f3TwampServerSecondaryState.name: f3TwampServerSecondaryState
f3TwampServerSecondaryState.description: Secondary state can be Active or SGEO. When Operational state is Normal this is Active. When Operational State is Outage then this is SGEO.

f3TwampServerAlias.name: f3TwampServerAlias
f3TwampServerAlias.description: An alias associated with the TWAMP Server.

f3TwampServerPort.name: f3TwampServerPort
f3TwampServerPort.description: This is the physical or logical port on which the Server and the corresponding Session Reflectors are associated with.

f3TwampServerStatus.name: f3TwampServerStatus
f3TwampServerStatus.description: This indicates the current state of the Server state machine.

f3TwampServerSessionIdleTimeout.name: f3TwampServerSessionIdleTimeout
f3TwampServerSessionIdleTimeout.description: When a TWAMP Test packet Is not received for this timeout period the TWAMP Session will go to IDLE state where Aging timer is started. This time is specified in seconds.

f3TwampServerSessionAgingTimeout.name: f3TwampServerSessionAgingTimeout
f3TwampServerSessionAgingTimeout.description: After a Session goes into IDLE state this timer with this timeout is started and on expiry the Session will terminate. This time is specified in seconds.

f3TwampServerActionObject.name: f3TwampServerActionObject
f3TwampServerActionObject.description: Object identfier used to specify the OID of a Session Reflector on which f3TwampServerAction should occur. Applicable for addSessReflector and rmvSessReflector actions.

f3TwampServerAction.name: f3TwampServerAction
f3TwampServerAction.description: User action performed on this Twamp Server instance. For addSessReflector and rmvSessReflector actions f3TwampServerActionObject has to be specified prior to setting this object.

f3TwampServerStorageType.name: f3TwampServerStorageType
f3TwampServerStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

f3TwampServerRowStatus.name: f3TwampServerRowStatus
f3TwampServerRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of f3TwampServerRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with f3TwampServerRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The f3TwampServerRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

f3TwampServerSessionReflectorTable.name: f3TwampServerSessionReflectorTable
f3TwampServerSessionReflectorTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Session Reflector entities associated with a TWAMP Server.

f3TwampServerSessionReflectorEntry.name: f3TwampServerSessionReflectorEntry
f3TwampServerSessionReflectorEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampServerSessionReflectorTable.

f3TwampServerSessionReflectorIndex.name: f3TwampServerSessionReflectorIndex
f3TwampServerSessionReflectorIndex.description: A unique index identifying the Session Reflector that is added to the Server. Note that this is not f3TwampSessionReflectorIndex.

f3TwampServerSessionReflector.name: f3TwampServerSessionReflector
f3TwampServerSessionReflector.description: This is the pointer to the Session Reflector added to the Server.

f3TwampSessionReflectorTable.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorTable
f3TwampSessionReflectorTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to TWAMP Session Reflector entities. This entity performs the functions of TWAMP Session Reflector which is to reflect TWAMP Test packets.

f3TwampSessionReflectorEntry.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorEntry
f3TwampSessionReflectorEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampSessionReflectorTable.

f3TwampSessionReflectorIndex.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorIndex
f3TwampSessionReflectorIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a TWAMP Session Reflector under the NE.

f3TwampSessionReflectorAdminState.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorAdminState
f3TwampSessionReflectorAdminState.description: All the state related attributes are added to support this entity being in outage state. But AdminState is always InService and is not editable.

f3TwampSessionReflectorOperationalState.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorOperationalState
f3TwampSessionReflectorOperationalState.description: Operational state can take Normal or Outage. When the TWAMP entity is operational then this is Normal. In some situations like a Card is unplugged and TWAMP entity is not operational this attribute goes to Outage state.

f3TwampSessionReflectorSecondaryState.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorSecondaryState
f3TwampSessionReflectorSecondaryState.description: Secondary state can be Active or SGEO. When Operational state is Normal this is Active. When Operational State is Outage then this is SGEO.

f3TwampSessionReflectorAlias.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorAlias
f3TwampSessionReflectorAlias.description: An alias associated with the TWAMP Session Reflector.

f3TwampSessionReflectorIpInterface.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorIpInterface
f3TwampSessionReflectorIpInterface.description: This is the IP interface used by SessionReflector. Session Reflector may use the same IP interface as any Control Client, Server, Session Sender or Session Reflector in the system as long as it has a unique UDP port.

f3TwampSessionReflectorUdpPort.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorUdpPort
f3TwampSessionReflectorUdpPort.description: This is the UDP Port used by the Session Reflector for TWAMP Test. The Combination of f3TwampSessionReflectorIpInterface and f3TwampSessionReflectorUdpPort shall be unique amongst all Session Senders and Session Reflectors on the system.

f3TwampSessionReflectorUseSenderSeqNum.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorUseSenderSeqNum
f3TwampSessionReflectorUseSenderSeqNum.description: TWAMP Light suggests that if the Session Reflector does not have the knowledge of the session state the Reflector has to copy the received sequence number into the Sequence Number field of the reflected TWAMP Test packet. This option is used if the Session Reflector is associated with a TwampServer which has f3TwampServerControlEnabled to true. If this is set to FALSE, the Session Reflector shall use its sequence number which is not reset until it rolls over. But there is an option for user to clear the sequence number.

f3TwampSessionReflectorUserCreated.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorUserCreated
f3TwampSessionReflectorUserCreated.description: When Session Reflector is created by the user this attribute will be set to true. If the Session Reflector is created as a consequence of Session request from the Control Client the Session Reflector is created by Server and this attribute is set to false.

f3TwampSessionReflectorStatus.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorStatus
f3TwampSessionReflectorStatus.description: This indicates the current state of the Session Reflector state machine.

f3TwampSessionReflectorAssocServer.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorAssocServer
f3TwampSessionReflectorAssocServer.description: This is the pointer to the associated TWAMP Server.

f3TwampSessionReflectorStorageType.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorStorageType
f3TwampSessionReflectorStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

f3TwampSessionReflectorRowStatus.name: f3TwampSessionReflectorRowStatus
f3TwampSessionReflectorRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of f3TwampSessionReflectorRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with f3TwampSessionReflectorRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The f3TwampSessionReflectorRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

f3TwampSessionTable.name: f3TwampSessionTable
f3TwampSessionTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to TWAMP Session entities. This entity represents a TWAMP Test session between a remote Session Sender and a local Session Reflector.

f3TwampSessionEntry.name: f3TwampSessionEntry
f3TwampSessionEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampSessionTable.

f3TwampSessionSsIpv4Address.name: f3TwampSessionSsIpv4Address
f3TwampSessionSsIpv4Address.description: IPv4 Address of the remote Session Sender. This with the f3TwampSessionUdpPort uniquely identifies a TWAMP test session between a remote Session Sender and local Session Reflector.

f3TwampSessionSsUdpPort.name: f3TwampSessionSsUdpPort
f3TwampSessionSsUdpPort.description: This is the UDP Port of the remote Session Sender. This with the f3TwampSessionIpv4Address uniquely identifies a TWAMP test session between a remote Session Sender and local Session Reflector.

f3TwampSessionStatus.name: f3TwampSessionStatus
f3TwampSessionStatus.description: This indicates the current state of the TWAMP Session state machine.

f3TwampSessionVlanEnabled.name: f3TwampSessionVlanEnabled
f3TwampSessionVlanEnabled.description: This indicates if the received TWAMP test packets have a VLAN Tag.

f3TwampSessionOuterVlanEtherType.name: f3TwampSessionOuterVlanEtherType
f3TwampSessionOuterVlanEtherType.description: This is the VLAN Tag Ethertype (TPID) of the outer VLAN tag of the received TWAMP test packets.

f3TwampSessionOuterVlanId.name: f3TwampSessionOuterVlanId
f3TwampSessionOuterVlanId.description: This is the outer VLAN ID of the received TWAMP test packets.

f3TwampSessionOuterVlanPriority.name: f3TwampSessionOuterVlanPriority
f3TwampSessionOuterVlanPriority.description: This is the outer VLAN Priority of the received TWAMP test packets.

f3TwampSessionInnerVlanEnabled.name: f3TwampSessionInnerVlanEnabled
f3TwampSessionInnerVlanEnabled.description: This indicates if the received TWAMP test packets have an inner VLAN tag.

f3TwampSessionInnerVlanEtherType.name: f3TwampSessionInnerVlanEtherType
f3TwampSessionInnerVlanEtherType.description: This is the VLAN Tag Ethertype (TPID) of the inner VLAN tag of the received TWAMP test packets.

f3TwampSessionInnerVlanId.name: f3TwampSessionInnerVlanId
f3TwampSessionInnerVlanId.description: This is the inner VLAN ID of the received TWAMP test packets.

f3TwampSessionInnerVlanPriority.name: f3TwampSessionInnerVlanPriority
f3TwampSessionInnerVlanPriority.description: This is the inner VLAN Priority of the received TWAMP test packets.

f3TwampSessionDscpValue.name: f3TwampSessionDscpValue
f3TwampSessionDscpValue.description: This is the DSCP value in the received TWAMP test packets.

f3TwampSessionSequenceNumber.name: f3TwampSessionSequenceNumber
f3TwampSessionSequenceNumber.description: This is the receive side sequence number that is set in the reflected TWAMP Test packet. This is incremented for each reflected TWAMP Test packet.

f3TwampSessionAction.name: f3TwampSessionAction
f3TwampSessionAction.description: This is the user action performed on this TWAMP Session instance.

f3TwampControlClientTable.name: f3TwampControlClientTable
f3TwampControlClientTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to TWAMP Control Client entities. This entity performs the functions of TWAMP Control Client when TWAMP Control protocol is enabled as defined in RFC 5357. This entity is created even when TWAMP Control is disabled as a container for Session Senders.

f3TwampControlClientEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampControlClientTable.

f3TwampControlClientIndex.name: f3TwampControlClientIndex
f3TwampControlClientIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a TWAMP Control Client under the NE.

f3TwampControlClientAdminState.name: f3TwampControlClientAdminState
f3TwampControlClientAdminState.description: All the state related attributes are added to support this entity being in outage state. But AdminState is always InService and is not editable.

f3TwampControlClientOperationalState.name: f3TwampControlClientOperationalState
f3TwampControlClientOperationalState.description: Operational state can take Normal or Outage. When the TWAMP entity is operational then this is Normal. In some situations like a Card is unplugged and TWAMP entity is not operational this attribute goes to Outage state.

f3TwampControlClientSecondaryState.name: f3TwampControlClientSecondaryState
f3TwampControlClientSecondaryState.description: Secondary state can be Active or SGEO. When Operational state is Normal this is Active. When Operational State is Outage then this is SGEO.

f3TwampControlClientAlias.name: f3TwampControlClientAlias
f3TwampControlClientAlias.description: An alias associated with the TWAMP Control Client.

f3TwampControlClientPort.name: f3TwampControlClientPort
f3TwampControlClientPort.description: This is the physical or logical port on which the Control Client and the corresponding Session Senders are associated with.

f3TwampControlClientStatus.name: f3TwampControlClientStatus
f3TwampControlClientStatus.description: This indicates the current state of the Control Client state machine.

f3TwampControlClientActionObject.name: f3TwampControlClientActionObject
f3TwampControlClientActionObject.description: Object identfier used to specify the OID of a Session Sender on which f3TwampControlClientAction should occur. Applicable for addSessSender and rmvSessSender actions.

f3TwampControlClientAction.name: f3TwampControlClientAction
f3TwampControlClientAction.description: User action performed on this Twamp Control Client instance. For addSessSender and rmvSessSender actions f3TwampControlClientActionObject has to be specified prior to setting this object.

f3TwampControlClientStorageType.name: f3TwampControlClientStorageType
f3TwampControlClientStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

f3TwampControlClientRowStatus.name: f3TwampControlClientRowStatus
f3TwampControlClientRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of f3TwampControlClientRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with f3TwampControlClientRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The f3TwampControlClientRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderTable.name: f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderTable
f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to Session Sender entities associated with a TWAMP Control Client.

f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderEntry.name: f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderEntry
f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderTable.

f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderIndex.name: f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderIndex
f3TwampControlClientSessionSenderIndex.description: A unique index identifying the Session Sender that is added to the Control Client. Note that this is not f3TwampSessionSenderIndex.

f3TwampControlClientSessionSender.name: f3TwampControlClientSessionSender
f3TwampControlClientSessionSender.description: This is the pointer to the Session Sender added to the Control Client.

f3TwampSessionSenderTable.name: f3TwampSessionSenderTable
f3TwampSessionSenderTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to TWAMP Session Sender entities. This entity performs the functions of TWAMP Session Sender which is to send TWAMP Test packets.

f3TwampSessionSenderEntry.name: f3TwampSessionSenderEntry
f3TwampSessionSenderEntry.description: A conceptual row in the f3TwampSessionSenderTable.

f3TwampSessionSenderIndex.name: f3TwampSessionSenderIndex
f3TwampSessionSenderIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify a TWAMP Session Sender under the NE.

f3TwampSessionSenderAdminState.name: f3TwampSessionSenderAdminState
f3TwampSessionSenderAdminState.description: All the state related attributes are added to support this entity being in outage state. But AdminState is always InService and is not editable.

f3TwampSessionSenderOperationalState.name: f3TwampSessionSenderOperationalState
f3TwampSessionSenderOperationalState.description: Operational state can take Normal or Outage. When the TWAMP entity is operational then this is Normal. In some situations like a Card is unplugged and TWAMP entity is not operational this attribute goes to Outage state.

f3TwampSessionSenderSecondaryState.name: f3TwampSessionSenderSecondaryState
f3TwampSessionSenderSecondaryState.description: Secondary state can be Active or SGEO. When Operational state is Normal this is Active. When Operational State is Outage then this is SGEO.

f3TwampSessionSenderAlias.name: f3TwampSessionSenderAlias
f3TwampSessionSenderAlias.description: An alias associated with the TWAMP Session Sender.

f3TwampSessionSenderIpInterface.name: f3TwampSessionSenderIpInterface
f3TwampSessionSenderIpInterface.description: This is the IP interface used by Session Sender. Session Sender may use the same IP interface as any Control Client, Server, Session Sender or Session Sender in the system as long as it has a unique UDP port.

f3TwampSessionSenderUdpPort.name: f3TwampSessionSenderUdpPort
f3TwampSessionSenderUdpPort.description: This is the UDP Port used by the Session Sender for TWAMP Test. The Combination of f3TwampSessionSenderIpInterface and f3TwampSessionSenderUdpPort shall be unique amongst all Session Senders and Session Reflectors on the system.

f3TwampSessionSenderPktSchedTimeInterval.name: f3TwampSessionSenderPktSchedTimeInterval
f3TwampSessionSenderPktSchedTimeInterval.description: This is the time interval between TWAMP-Test packets.

f3TwampSessionSenderSrIpv4Address.name: f3TwampSessionSenderSrIpv4Address
f3TwampSessionSenderSrIpv4Address.description: This is the IPv4 address of the Session Reflector.

f3TwampSessionSenderSrUdpPort.name: f3TwampSessionSenderSrUdpPort
f3TwampSessionSenderSrUdpPort.description: This is the UDP Port recommended by the Session Sender for the Session Reflector for TWAMP Test.

f3TwampSessionSenderDscpValue.name: f3TwampSessionSenderDscpValue
f3TwampSessionSenderDscpValue.description: This is the TWAMP Test packet DSCP value to be used in the IP header. This is read-create when the TWAMP Control is disabled. When TWAMP Control is enabled this will be read-only and will have the same as the DSCP value of the Control Client.

f3TwampSessionSenderNumPkts.name: f3TwampSessionSenderNumPkts
f3TwampSessionSenderNumPkts.description: This is the number TWAMP test packets to send for test session.

f3TwampSessionSenderPktSize.name: f3TwampSessionSenderPktSize
f3TwampSessionSenderPktSize.description: This is the size of the TWAMP test packet. For unauthenticated mode, Minimum is the 18 (Eth Hdr) + 20 (IP Hdr) + 41 (TWAMP) Bytes. The TWAMP test packet will be padded to the specified size.

f3TwampSessionSenderTestPattern.name: f3TwampSessionSenderTestPattern
f3TwampSessionSenderTestPattern.description: This the pattern of the bytes in the padding of the TWAMP Test packet.

f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType.name: f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType
f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType.description: This indicates the start time type which tells how to interpret the start time attribute. If IMMEDIATE, f3TwampSessionSenderStartTime is not applicable If RELATIVE, f3TwampSessionSenderStartTime is the relative to current time If FIXED, f3TwampSessionSenderStartTime is the wall clock start time

f3TwampSessionSenderStartDate.name: f3TwampSessionSenderStartDate
f3TwampSessionSenderStartDate.description: This is the date part of the Session Sender start time. When TWAMP Control is enabled, the Date and Time are converted to the NTP timestamp format as defined in RFC 1305 [REF13] to send in Request-TW-Session message. The first 32 bits are the seconds since 0h Jan 1 1900 and the second 32 bits is the fractional second and is the number of units of 200 picoseconds. If f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType is IMMEDIATE, this attribute is not applicable. If f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType is RELATIVE, this attribute is not applicable. If f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType is FIXED, this attribute is the date when to start the test.

f3TwampSessionSenderStartTime.name: f3TwampSessionSenderStartTime
f3TwampSessionSenderStartTime.description: This is the time part of the Session Sender start time. When TWAMP Control is enabled, the Date and Time are converted to the NTP timestamp format as defined in RFC 1305 [REF13] to send in Request-TW-Session message. The first 32 bits are the seconds since 0h Jan 1 1900 and the second 32 bits is the fractional second and is the number of units of 200 picoseconds. If f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType is IMMEDIATE, this attribute is not applicable. If f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType is RELATIVE, this attribute is not applicable. If f3TwampSessionSenderStartTimeType is FIXED, this attribute is the time when to start the test.

f3TwampSessionSenderRespTimeout.name: f3TwampSessionSenderRespTimeout
f3TwampSessionSenderRespTimeout.description: This is how much time the Session Sender will wait for the response to a TWAMP Test packet. In effect the TWAMP Test is complete after Test Duration + Response Timeout.

f3TwampSessionSenderVlanEnabled.name: f3TwampSessionSenderVlanEnabled
f3TwampSessionSenderVlanEnabled.description: This indicates whether the TWAMP Test packets are tagged or not.

f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanId.name: f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanId
f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanId.description: This specifies the outer VLAN ID. This is applicable if f3TwampSessionSenderVlanEnabled is true.

f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanPriority.name: f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanPriority
f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanPriority.description: This specifies the outer VLAN priority. This is applicable if f3TwampSessionSenderVlanEnabled is true.

f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanEtherType.name: f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanEtherType
f3TwampSessionSenderOuterVlanEtherType.description: This specifies the outer VLAN tag Ethertype/TPID. This is applicable if f3TwampSessionSenderVlanEnabled is true.

f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEnabled.name: f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEnabled
f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEnabled.description: This indicates whether the TWAMP Test packets are double tagged or not. This is applicable only if f3TwampSessionSenderVlanEnabled is true.

f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanId.name: f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanId
f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanId.description: This specifies the inner VLAN ID. This is applicable if f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEnabled is true.

f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanPriority.name: f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanPriority
f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanPriority.description: This specifies the inner VLAN priority. This is applicable if f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEnabled is true.

f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEtherType.name: f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEtherType
f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEtherType.description: This specifies the outer VLAN tag Ethertype/TPID. This is applicable if f3TwampSessionSenderInnerVlanEnabled is true.

f3TwampSessionSenderSeqNumber.name: f3TwampSessionSenderSeqNumber
f3TwampSessionSenderSeqNumber.description: This is the session sender sequence number that is set in the generated TWAMP Test packet.

f3TwampSessionSenderStatus.name: f3TwampSessionSenderStatus
